  "body": "Reproduction steps:\r\n\r\n1. Create a hardhat repo and add a `mainnet` network and a mainnet forking config\r\n2. Run this script with and without `--network mainnet`:\r\n\r\n    ```javascript\r\n    async function main() {\r\n      const blockNumber = \"0xc88112\"\r\n\r\n      const feeHistory = await network.provider.send(\"eth_feeHistory\", [\r\n        \"0x1\",\r\n        blockNumber,\r\n        [25, 75]\r\n      ])\r\n\r\n      console.log(JSON.stringify(feeHistory.reward, null, 2));\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    main()\r\n      .then(() => process.exit(0))\r\n      .catch(error => {\r\n        console.error(error);\r\n        process.exit(1);\r\n      });\r\n    ```\r\n3. In mainnet, the result is `[\"0x66f51f96\", \"0x514987956\"]` while in forked mainnet is `[\"0x1dcd650000\", \"0x34b409e278\"]`. Notice that the values are much higher in the forked mainnet.",
